ed with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes was born about 1295, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Thomas Falconer. She died after 1324."},"et":{"about 1295–AFT 1324":"umbes 1295–pärast 1324","1295–1346":"1295–1346","1320–1369":"1320–1369","1334–1401":"1334–1401","1295–1324":"1295–1324","1369":"1369","1324":"1324","1401":"1401","1346":"1346","AFT 1324":"pärast 1324","1334":"1334","ABT 1320":"umbes 1320","1320":"1320","1295":"1295","about 1295":"umbes 1295","Of England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Thurcaston, Leics, Eng":"Thurcaston, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1295–AFT 1324":"noin 1295–1324 jälkeen","1295–1346":"1295–1346","1320–1369":"1320–1369","1334–1401":"1334–1401","1295–1324":"1295–1324","1369":"1369","1324":"1324","1401":"1401","1346":"1346","AFT 1324":"1324 jälkeen","1334":"1334","ABT 1320":"noin 1320","1320":"1320","1295":"1295","about 1295":"noin 1295","Of England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Thurcaston, Leics, Eng":"Thurcaston, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1295–AFT 1324":"environ 1295–après 1324","1295–1346":"1295–1346","1320–1369":"1320–1369","1334–1401":"1334–1401","1295–1324":"1295–1324","1369":"1369","1324":"1324","1401":"1401","1346":"1346","AFT 1324":"après 1324","1334":"1334","ABT 1320":"environ 1320","1320":"1320","1295":"1295","about 1295":"environ 1295","Of England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","of Thurcaston, Leics, Eng":"Thurcaston, Leicestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Agnes est née environ 1295, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils a